  "description": "Hartington sausages are speciality blue cheese sausages from a village in the Peak District, revered for it's creameries and cheese production. You'll serve them with an Irish classic: colcannon (mashed potatoes with spring greens and onion), topped off with an apple an chive compote. Perfect comfort food if you're feeling a little 'blue'. ",
